The paper focuses on keyphrase extraction from scholarly articles, which is a task commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) community. The use of deep contextualized embeddings and sequence labeling techniques are also common in NLP research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, as keyphrase extraction is a sub-task of IR. This suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning models such as BiLSTM-CRF and BERT also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on embeddings and self-attention layers suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
